You're right — `Ctrl+P` is VS Code's "Quick Open" file finder, so it likely gets intercepted before reaching Claude Code.

You can rebind the model picker to a custom shortcut. Edit `~/.claude/keybindings.json`:

```json
{
  "bindings": [
    {
      "context": "Chat",
      "bindings": {
        "ctrl+m": "chat:modelPicker"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

That would make `Ctrl+M` open the model picker when the Claude Code panel is focused. Pick whatever key combo doesn't conflict with VS Code.
